Female can be recognized by its medium to small body size (7.83-10.39 mm); rough clypeus with median carina, apical margin crenulate (Fig. 
33b
); mandibles four teeth with two stout apical teeth at apex and two small teeth basally; labrum rectangular (Fig. 
33c
); metasoma covered with ferruginous hairs (Fig. 
33e
); scopa ferruginous except white basal area (Fig. 
33f
).

